On Wednesday, July 06, 2005, at 03:21PM, Mike Benthin <benthin(-at-)prodigy.net> wrote:

>So what is the proper way to adjust these-adjust fully closed on your 
>coldest day, or just fully open at "fully hot" like after your oil temp 
>has reached 220 and thermostat is maximally expanded?  I've done the 
>latter and then it doesn't seem to fully close in winter.......but then 
>here in NJ it rarely goes below 20 deg...

VW says to do it cold but I usually tweak the cable a second time when hot. The idea is to remove some of the slack in order to prevent it accidentally coming off the pulley.

